sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist<br/>Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy<br/>Authentication
    participant Service as notebook Service<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant Jupyter as Jupyter Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant PyPI as PyPI/Conda<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Jupyter: Flow 1: User Access to Jupyter Workbench

    User->>Router: GET /notebook/{namespace}/{username}/<br/>HTTPS/443
    Router->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>TLS 1.2+ terminated
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth token
    OAuth->>Service: Forward with token<br/>HTTP/8888 (internal)
    Service->>Jupyter: Proxy to container<br/>HTTP/8888
    Jupyter->>Jupyter: Load JupyterLab UI<br/>Optional token validation
    Jupyter-->>Service: JupyterLab interface<br/>HTML/JS/WebSocket
    Service-->>OAuth: Response
    OAuth-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: JupyterLab interface<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over User,Jupyter: Interactive notebook session (WebSocket)
    User->>Router: WebSocket upgrade<br/>HTTPS/443
    Router->>OAuth: WebSocket with token
    OAuth->>Service: Authenticated WebSocket
    Service->>Jupyter: WebSocket to kernel
    Jupyter-->>User: Kernel responses via WebSocket

    Note over Jupyter,PyPI: Runtime package installation
    Jupyter->>PyPI: pip install {package}<br/>HTTPS/443
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Package files<br/>TLS 1.2+

    participant KFP as Kubeflow Pipelines<br/>Pipeline Execution
    participant Runtime as Runtime Image Pod<br/>Bootstrapper
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>S3/Minio

    Note over KFP,S3: Flow 2: Pipeline Execution (Runtime Images)

    KFP->>Runtime: Start pod with runtime image<br/>Python/Notebook execution
    Runtime->>Runtime: Execute bootstrapper.py<br/>Elyra initialization

    Runtime->>S3: GET dependencies.tar.gz<br/>HTTPS/443 or HTTP/9000
    Note right of S3: Auth: AWS IAM or Static Creds<br/>Encryption: TLS 1.2+ or None
    S3-->>Runtime: Dependencies archive
    Runtime->>Runtime: Extract and install<br/>pip/conda

    Runtime->>S3: GET input artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 or HTTP/9000
    S3-->>Runtime: Input data files

    Runtime->>Runtime: Execute notebook/script<br/>papermill/python3/Rscript
    Runtime->>Runtime: Generate outputs<br/>Results, plots, metadata

    Runtime->>S3: PUT output artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443 or HTTP/9000
    Runtime->>S3: PUT HTML reports<br/>HTTPS/443 or HTTP/9000
    Runtime->>S3: PUT KFP metadata<br/>HTTPS/443 or HTTP/9000
    S3-->>Runtime: Upload confirmations
    Runtime-->>KFP: Exit code 0<br/>Success

    participant CodeUser as Data Scientist<br/>Browser
    participant CodeRouter as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CodeService as notebook Service<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant NGINX as NGINX Proxy<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CodeServer as code-server<br/>localhost:8080 HTTP

    Note over CodeUser,CodeServer: Flow 3: code-server Access

    CodeUser->>CodeRouter: GET /<br/>HTTPS/443
    CodeRouter->>OAuth: TLS termination<br/>OAuth validation
    OAuth->>CodeService: Forward authenticated<br/>HTTP/8888
    CodeService->>NGINX: Proxy to NGINX<br/>HTTP/8080
    NGINX->>CodeServer: Reverse proxy<br/>localhost:8080
    CodeServer-->>NGINX: VS Code interface<br/>HTML/JS/WebSocket
    NGINX-->>CodeService: Response
    CodeService-->>OAuth: Response
    OAuth-->>CodeRouter: Response
    CodeRouter-->>CodeUser: VS Code in browser<br/>HTTPS/443

    Note over NGINX,CodeServer: Health check flow
    NGINX->>NGINX: GET /healthz<br/>Internal health endpoint
    NGINX-->>NGINX: 200 OK<br/>Service healthy
